# Design user preference storage

## Description
Design a schema for storing user preferences including communication style, format preferences, domain expertise levels, and interaction patterns. Preferences should be scoped per user-agent combination.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Create `PagServer.Schema.UserPreference` with fields for user_id, agent_id, preference_type, value, confidence, metadata
- [ ] Define preference types: communication_style, format_preference, expertise_level, language_preference, detail_level
- [ ] Add confidence scoring (0.0-1.0) for learned vs explicit preferences
- [ ] Include source tracking (explicit, inferred, learned)
- [ ] Database migration created and tested
- [ ] Add indexes for efficient user-agent queries
- [ ] Tests pass
- [ ] Lint passes

